<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12118c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12118c">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12118c"> 118(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> his knife &amp; porringer</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> le dioc&egrave;se et la ville de Bobbio restent fid&egrave;les &agrave; la m&eacute;moire de leur patron, de leur bienfaiteur insigne; l&apos;&eacute;glise abbatiale, devenue paroissiale, conserve avec un soin diligent, sur le ma&icirc;tre- autel de la crypte, la ch&acirc;sse et son pr&eacute;cieux d&eacute;p&ocirc;t, comme dans son tr&eacute;sor, l&apos;&eacute;cuelle de bois et le couteau qui passent pour avoir servi au bienheureux. <br><font color="green">[&hellip; the diocese and the town of Bobbio remained faithful to the memory of their master, their distinguished benefactor. The abbatial church, which became parochial, diligently preserved the shrine and its precious deposit on the high altar of the crypt as well as his relics, <mark>the wooden bowl and the knife</mark> that are supposed to have been used by the saint.]</font> <small> <a name="STCM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#STCM"><cite title="source">Saint Colomban</cite></a> (1905) 195</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
